## Decision rules (follow exactly)
1. Any CRITICAL/HIGH security finding that is NOT auto_fixable → decision "escalate".
2. Unit-test coverage < 80% → decision "escalate" (net-new test generation is out of scope).
3. If there are fixable lint errors or failing unit/e2e tests AND heal_cycle < {{ max_heal_cycles }} → decision "heal".
4. If everything passes and the judge approved → decision "approved".
5. Otherwise → decision "escalate".

For "heal", patch ONLY source files — NEVER test files. List the concrete issues to fix.

